.NET Framework 3.5.name: SDK_SimHeadset
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The Sim Headset SDK script provides dummy functions for the headset.

methods.name: AddHeadsetFade(Transform camera)
methods.summary: The AddHeadsetFade method attempts to add the fade functionality to the game object with the camera on it.

params.value: The Transform to with the camera on to add the fade functionality to.

methods.name: GetHeadset()
methods.summary: The GetHeadset method returns the Transform of the object that is used to represent the headset in the scene.
methods.returns: A transform of the object representing the headset in the scene.

methods.name: GetHeadsetAngularVelocity()
methods.summary: The GetHeadsetAngularVelocity method is used to determine the current angular velocity of the headset.
methods.returns: A Vector3 containing the current angular velocity of the headset.

methods.name: GetHeadsetCamera()
methods.summary: The GetHeadsetCamera/0 method returns the Transform of the object that is used to hold the headset camera in the scene.
methods.returns: A transform of the object holding the headset camera in the scene.

methods.name: GetHeadsetVelocity()
methods.summary: The GetHeadsetVelocity method is used to determine the current velocity of the headset.
methods.returns: A Vector3 containing the current velocity of the headset.

methods.name: HasHeadsetFade(Transform obj)
methods.summary: The HasHeadsetFade method checks to see if the given game object (usually the camera) has the ability to fade the viewpoint.
methods.returns: Returns true if the headset has fade functionality on it.

params.value: The Transform to check to see if a camera fade is available on.

methods.name: HeadsetFade(Color color, float duration, bool fadeOverlay)
methods.summary: The HeadsetFade method is used to apply a fade to the headset camera to progressively change the colour.

params.value: The amount of time the fade should take to reach the given colour.
Determines whether to use an overlay on the fade.

methods.syntax: public void HeadsetFade(Color color, float duration, bool fadeOverlay)
methods.linkedSyntax: public void HeadsetFade(Color color, float duration, bool fadeOverlay)

methods.name: ProcessFixedUpdate(Dictionary<string, object> options)
methods.summary: The ProcessFixedUpdate method enables an SDK to run logic for every Unity FixedUpdate

params.value: A dictionary of generic options that can be used to within the fixed update.

methods.name: ProcessUpdate(Dictionary<string, object> options)
methods.summary: The ProcessUpdate method enables an SDK to run logic for every Unity Update

params.value: A dictionary of generic options that can be used to within the update.
